# Backend Conventions (Laravel 12)

## Architecture layers (strict)
- **Controllers** → receive, delegate, return only. No business logic, no Eloquent queries.
- **FormRequests** → all validation lives here (one per action). Never inline `$request->validate()`.
- **Services** → business logic. One service per domain area.
- **Repositories** → all Eloquent queries. Controllers and services never query models directly.
- **DTOs** → typed input across layer boundaries. Services accept DTOs, not raw arrays.
- **API Resources** → all responses wrapped in `ApiResponse::success()` / `ApiResponse::error()`.

## File locations
| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Controllers | `backend/app/Http/Controllers/` |
| FormRequests | `backend/app/Http/Requests/` |
| Services | `backend/app/Services/` |
| Repositories | `backend/app/Repositories/` |
| DTOs | `backend/app/DTOs/` |
| API Resources | `backend/app/Http/Resources/` |
| Models | `backend/app/Models/` |
| Support classes | `backend/app/Support/` |

## AI driver
Always use `AiProviderInterface` — never call Groq/Ollama directly.
The active driver is resolved via `AI_DRIVER=stub|groq|ollama` env var.
Stub provider must always work without any API keys (used in tests).

## Social publishers
Each publisher lives in `backend/app/Services/Social/Publishers/`.
Implement `PublisherInterface`. Register in `SocialPublisherService`.
Use `MediaUrlClassifier` to validate media URLs before publishing.

## Testing
- Feature tests in `backend/tests/Feature/`, unit tests in `backend/tests/Unit/`
- Always use `RefreshDatabase` + `Sanctum::actingAs()` for authenticated endpoints
- Mock HTTP calls with `Http::fake()` — never hit real APIs in tests
- Run: `docker compose exec backend php artisan test`

## Code quality
```bash
composer lint       # pint --test (dry-run check)
composer lint:fix   # pint (auto-format)
composer analyse    # phpstan level 6
```
